    • Field Detail

      • layer

        @Option
public LayerEnum layer
        Specifies whether images are drawn below or above traces. When "xref" and "yref" are both set to "paper", image is drawn below the entire plot area.

        Default: ABOVE

      • opacity

        @Option
public Double opacity
        The opacity of the image.

        Constraints: ≥0 and ≤1

        Default: 1

      • sizex

        @Option
public Integer sizex
        The image container size horizontally. The image will be sized based on the "position" value. When "xref" is set to "paper", units are sized relative to the plot width.

        Default: 0

      • sizey

        @Option
public Integer sizey
        The image container size vertically. The image will be sized based on the "position" value. When "yref" is set to "paper", units are sized relative to the plot height.

        Default: 0

      • sizing

        @Option
public ImageOptions.SizingEnum sizing
        Specifies which dimension of the image to constrain.

      • source

        @Option
public String source
        Specifies the URL of the image to be used. The URL must be accessible from the domain where the plot code is run, and can be either relative or absolute.

      • visible

        @Option
public Boolean visible
        Determines whether or not this image is visible.

        Default: true

      • x

        @Option
public Double x
        The image's x position. When "xref" is set to "paper", units are sized relative to the plot height. See "xref" for more info.

        Default: 0

      • xanchor

        @Option
public HorizontalAlignEnum xanchor
        The anchor for the x position.

        Default: LEFT

      • xref

        @Option
public String xref
        The images's x coordinate axis. If set to a x axis id (e.g. "x" or "x2"), the "x" position refers to an x data coordinate If set to "paper", the "x" position refers to the distance from the left of plot in normalized coordinates where "0" ("1") corresponds to the left (right).

        Constraints: "paper" | "/^x([2-9]|[1-9][0-9]+)?$/"

        Default: "paper"

      • y

        @Option
public Double y
        The image's y position. When "yref" is set to "paper", units are sized relative to the plot width. See "yref" for more info.

        Default: 0

      • yanchor

        @Option
public VerticalAlignEnum yanchor
        The anchor for the y position.

        Default: TOP

      • yref

        @Option
public String yref
        The images's y coordinate axis. If set to a y axis id (e.g. "y" or "y2"), the "y" position refers to a y data coordinate. If set to "paper", the "y" position refers to the distance from the bottom of the plot in normalized coordinates where "0" ("1") corresponds to the bottom (top).

        Constraints: "paper" | "/^x([2-9]|[1-9][0-9]+)?$/"

        Default: "paper"
